# Java Conventions

## Package Layout

| Package | Responsibility |
|---------|---------------|
| `za.driver.model` | Entities, value objects, enums |
| `za.driver.persistence` | JSON read/write, repositories |
| `za.driver.scoring` | Metric calculators, ScoringService |
| `za.driver.import_` | Import wrapper, validation, ImportService |
| `za.driver.service` | Business logic orchestration |
| `za.driver.ui` | Swing frames, panels, dialogs |

## Rules

- Enum and field names must match `docs/data_dictionary.md` exactly
- Use `java.util.UUID`, `java.time.LocalDate`, `java.time.LocalDateTime`, `BigDecimal` for price
- Jackson for all JSON; no manual string parsing
- `scoring/` and `import_/` must not import any Swing classes
- File I/O and scoring off the EDT — use `SwingWorker`
- Derived metric fields on `Vehicle` are read-only in the UI

## Testing

- JUnit 5 for `scoring/` and `import_/` — required
- Round-trip serialization tests for `persistence/`
- Run `mvn test` before marking a phase complete

## Example

```java
// scoring/ must stay UI-free
public final class ScoringService {
    public DerivedMetrics calculate(Vehicle vehicle, ScoringProfile profile) { ... }
}

// UI delegates to service, never to repository directly
new SwingWorker<Vehicle, Void>() {
    protected Vehicle doInBackground() {
        return vehicleService.save(vehicle);
    }
    protected void done() { refreshTable(); }
}.execute();
```
